value.value: Human BST2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 19p13.11 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes bone marrow stromal antigen 2, plays a role in the negative regulation of viral infectivity.
Bone marrow stromal antigen 2 (180 aa, ~20 kDa) is encoded by the human BST2 gene. This protein is involved in preventing the release of virions from infected cells.

An assay based on Antibody-Dependent Cellular Cytotoxicity, which involves the killing of a target cell by a killer cell.  This is accomplished via an antibody directed to the target by the antigen-binding arms and anchored to the killer cell via an Fc receptor.

label.value: Myeloblasts 5 Percent or Less of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that 5 percent or less of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.
